 <hr id="ligne">
<p > <a href="Employee_Incentive_Program.htm" ><img  class="imageflottane" src="images/Employee Incentive Program.jpg" alt="Employee Incentive Program" Title="Employee Incentive Program"/></a> <div id="imageleftparagraphe"> Implementing an employee incentive program  in your company can be done in many ways, but the common denominator is the results: increased productivity. A recent article in the Harvard Business Review "Leadership That Gets Results," reported that of six leadership styles studied, the use of rewards was the single highest predictor of "organizational climate," which in turn had a direct correlation with financial results.</div></p>

<p>Most employee incentive programs in the workplace are home-made and not monitored properly. Let Loyalty Source and it's team of experts guide you in creating a targeted selection of rewards that your employees value and will work harder to achieve.</p>

<a class="lien" href="homePage.htm" style="margin-left:0px;" >Contact Our Experts for a Free Consultation Employee Incentive Programs</a> 
<div class="paragraphe1" >
<h4 id="titre">How to Get the Most Out of your Employee Incentive Program</h4>  
<p class="paragraphe">Employee incentive programs are debatably the best non-monetary way to stimulate and recognize your workforce. The only downside is these incentive programs often are not updated and the offer loses its appeal with time.

</p><br>

<p>The incentives offered to employees  need to be fresh and current. Loyalty Source can offer you weekly, monthly or yearly  product updates for your employee incentive program. Offering popular products from top performing brands in your employee incentive program is crucial to achieving your program objectives.

</p>
